data.title: Alexandra Chando Celebrity News and Gossip
data.text:
Josh Duhamel keeps it cool and casual while attending the premiere of his latest film Buddy Games held at the 2019 Mammoth Film Festival on Sunday (February 10) in Mammoth Lakes, Calif.

The 46-year-old actor, who also wrote and directed the flick, was joined at the event by Ashley Greene and her husband Paul Khoury, Kat Graham, Kevin Dillon, Chris Zylka, Ramsey Krull, Ryan Rottman, Skyler Samuels and Dylan Efron.

The evening before, Josh and the rest of the stars took part in the Mammoth Media Institute Charity Celebrity Bowling Tournament and were also joined by Adelaide Kane, Alexandra Chando, Blair Redford, Cassie Scerbo, Xzibit, Stephen Colletti, Brock O’Hurn and Jonathan Keltz. The bowling tournament was hosted by Cameo.

Also pictured: Jennifer Morrison, Jessica Szohr, Ryan, Adelaide and more stopping by the Mammoth Film Festival suite to peruse Strong On Health nutritional subscription boxes.

Ashley Tisdale cozies up to husband Christopher French inside Amazon Prime Video’s Golden Globe Awards After Party held at The Beverly Hilton Hotel on Sunday night (January 6) in Beverly Hills, Calif.

The 32-year-old producer, singer and beauty maven highlighted her cotton candy pink hair for the annual bash, celebrating the 2019 Golden Globe Awards.

PHOTOS: Check out the latest pics of Ashley Tisdale

Riverdale actress Vanessa Morgan, Alexandra Chando, Kat Graham and Chloe Bennet are also pictured below at the InStyle And Warner Bros. Golden Globes After Party.

FYI: Ashley is wearing a Chalayan dress and Dannijo earrings. Vanessa‘s black dress was a Redemption gown, Brian Atwood heels, Rock Her earrings, Norman Silverman rings and Jimmy Choo clutch. Her second look was a Marc Bower gown, Norman Silverman diamond hoops, Rock Her ring, Edie Parker clutch and Jimmy Choo heels. Kat is wearing a Genny dress, Jimmy Choo shoes, and Lorraine Schwartz jewelry. Alexandra is wearing a Bronx and Banco dress. Chloe is wearing a Markarian dress and Kallati jewelry.

25+ pictures inside of Ashley Tisdale and Christopher French…

Zoe Kravitz goes bold with a bright red lip as she celebrates her new role with Yves Saint Laurent Beauty at Gibson Brands Sunset on Wednesday night (May 18) in Los Angeles.

The 27-year-old Divergent star was joined by Hailee Steinfeld, Kelly Osbourne, Alexandra Chando, RJ Mitte, and singer Cailee Rae.

Zoe shared an Instagram photo of herself performing with her band Lolawolf, and wrote, “#LOLAWOLF • #yslbeauty • thank you for the lovely evening ! @yslbeauty • �’�🏾”

Check it out below!

Tom Welling keeps it cool and casual as he hits the red carpet at the 6 Bullets to Hell Mobile Game Launch Party held on Tuesday (May 10) in Los Angeles.

The 39-year-old actor was joined at the event by Ashley Greene and her boyfriend Paul Khoury, Ryan Rottman, Alexandra Chando, Sean Faris and his girlfriend Cherie Jimenez, Allie Gonino, Arielle Vandenberg, Blair Redford and Cassie Scerbo.

PHOTOS: Check out the latest pics of Tom Welling

“@tessmer ripping for #6bulletstohell #compliments of @timnewfang,” Tom captioned with his Instagram post of his pal Eric Tessmer hitting the stage at the event.

35+ pictures inside of Tom Welling, Ashley Greene and others at the launch party…More Here! »

Michael Trevino carries several bags out of Ralph’s after stopping for some groceries for Labor Day on Monday afternoon (September 7) in Los Angeles.

The 30-year-old Vampire Diaries actor was joined by The Lying Game alum Alexandra Chando, who walked alongside him holding several bags as well.

It’s unclear whether Michael and Alexandra are dating or not, but we do know they’ve been friends for several years.

In fact, Alexandra starred on As the World Turns with his good pal and TVD co-star Zach Roerig!

In case you didn’t know, Michael was previously linked to Glee‘s Jenna Ushkowitz for over three years before they broke up back in May 2014.

Ed Westwick is suave in a leather jacket while attending the 2015 Pieces Of Heaven Art Auction presented by The Art Of Elysium and Samsung Galaxy at MAMA Gallery on Tuesday (February 17) in Los Angeles.

The 27-year-old English actor was joined by Rose McGowan and Alexandra Chando at the event, where approximately 70 pieces of artwork were donated to be auctioned.

PHOTOS: Check out the latest pics of Ed Westwick

During the auction, Ed and Rose caught up over cocktails and used the Samsung Galaxy Note 4 to learn more about the artists from the live auction lots, such as Shepard Fairey, Sage Vaughn, and Chris Cran.
